	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000966_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>57 Sloane St</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">3<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">d </hi></hi> March 1857 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>D<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> Shaw</persName></p>
<lb/><p>On recollecting your 
<lb/>kind notice that I might 
<lb/>draw some money 
<lb/>from the testimonial 
<lb/>fund through you 
<lb/>and having nothing 
<lb/>else at present in 
<lb/>my power unless 
<lb/>I should begin to 
<lb/>draw afresh from 
<lb/>the L. Mission Society 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000966_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/>or from <persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName>
<lb/>the publisher, I shall 
<lb/>feel much obliged 
<lb/>if you can let me 
<lb/>have £50 of the money 
<lb/>in your hands without 
<lb/>making it much 
<lb/>known. If it should 
<lb/>be necessary to discuss 
<lb/>the thing before 
<lb/>committees you 
<lb/>need not take the 
<lb/>trouble, but return 
<lb/>the receipt by <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">rs</hi></hi> L.</persName></p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_000966_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'-->
<lb/><p>I might apply to the 
<lb/>London Missionary 
<lb/>society but it would 
<lb/>be beginning the 
<lb/>£100 for 1857 which 
<lb/>I have no intention 
<lb/>of doing. I have 
<lb/>nothing now there 
<lb/>as they gave part of 
<lb/>my salary to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi> L.</persName>
<lb/>when I was absent 
<lb/>and the sum (£100) 
<lb/>I had over of my 
<lb/>four years trip is 
<lb/>now among the things 
<lb/>that were 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_000966_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'--> 
<lb/>this £50 if it can be 
<lb/>got without trouble 
<lb/>and talk, will enable 
<lb/>us to go on till we 
<lb/>get more into our 
<lb/>hands either from 
<lb/>the book or testimonial<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I am busy at work 
<lb/>never out scarcely, 
<lb/>am going to the Arch bishop<reg>'</reg>s 
<lb/>tonight and as I am 
<lb/>not sure about the 
<lb/>"<hi rend="underline">stone</hi>" &amp; "ston" I imitate 
<lb/>him &amp; sign myself </p>
<lb/><p rend="center">David Zambezi </p>
			
